RESEARCH turns your data into a dataset you can analyze and get results and saved artifacts (charts, tables, docs). Once your tickets CSV is a dataset, you can run queries, tests, and produce summaries.

To import your CSV, I need:
1) The absolute file path to the CSV
2) A one‑line description of what’s inside (e.g., “Zendesk tickets 2023–2025 with id, created_at, subject, body, status, assignee, tags”)

Optional but helpful: note which column is the ticket ID and the main text field.

Once you give me the path and description, I will:
- Inspect the file to infer schema and sample rows
- Register a dataset and upload the file
- Deploy it so it’s ready for queries and analyses

